            <h1>Your Security</h1>
            <p style="max-width:450px">In modern day many people stress about issues of cyber threats, <b>doxxing</b>, <b>ddosing</b> on their home network through methods they do not understand
            and do not know how to prevent, someblogagain is blog site which will eliminate this factor making a database which contains no personal identifiable information about you
            someblogagain aims to allow users to express their thoughts freely without having to deal with potential consequence of being hacked, doxxed, booted offline.</p>

            <h1>Creating Account Privacy</h1>
            <p style="max-width:450px">When making an account on websites' majority of time a lot of your data is backend stored this includes IPs, User-Agents, Names and other personal
            information which if leaked could be used to, find more information about you and find your passwords in data breaches. Someblogagain aims to counter this problem by providing you
            a random set of numbers 32 characters long which will be used to authenticate you, the backend will only store posts correlated to the account and the account number.</p>
        
